Chessy - Cyberpunk Chess Game
Overview
Chessy is a cyberpunk-themed chess game developed in Python.
It offers two exciting modes: play with a friend or against a computer.
The game features animations, sound effects, and a stylish interface designed for an immersive experience.

Features:
Sound effects and animated chess piece motions.
Particular sound effects for: Movements of the pieces.
catching fragments.
keeping oneself in check.
All chess moves are shown on a separate side screen.
A Learn section featuring well-known openings in chess.
Shortcuts on the keyboard to improve gameplay:
Z: Reverse the previous action.
R: Restart the game.
All noises may be turned on or off using the Settings menu.
The logos of the project team and the university are displayed on the startup screen.
Title of the game: Chessy.

Getting Started
Prerequisites
Python 3.8 or higher.
The following Python libraries:
pygame
Installation
Clone the repository:
bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/chessy.git
Navigate to the project directory:
bash
Copy code
cd chessy
Install required dependencies:
bash
Copy code
pip install pygame

Running the Game
Run the main Python script to start the game:
bash
Copy code
python main.py

Gameplay Instructions
Main Menu
Play:
Choose to play against a friend or the computer.
Learn:
Explore famous chess openings with descriptions.
Settings:
Enable or disable all game sounds.
During Gameplay
Use the mouse to move pieces by dragging them to valid positions.
Keyboard shortcuts:
Z: Undo the last move.
R: Reset the game.

Starter Screen for Games:

includes the emblems of your team and institution, then the game name "Chessy."
opens the main menu.

Board for Chess:
displays a chessboard with a cyberpunk motif.
On a side screen, moves are recorded in real time.
Section on Learning:
uses interactive features to highlight well-known chess openings.

Configuration:

Turn on or off the sound effects.
Details of the Features and Sound Effects
special sound effects for captures and piece movements.
When a player is in check, a unique sound is produced.
Reset and Undo
Use the Z key to reverse the previous action.
Use the R key to restart the game.
Study well-known chess openings, such as the Queen's Gambit and the Sicilian Defense.

